textDelta: what is active listening? Active listening is a communication skill that allows you to understand what someone is saying and to feel heard. It is a way of communicating that involves listening carefully, reflecting back what was said, and asking questions to clarify. Active listening allows you to: • Understand what someone is saying • Feel heard • Clarify information • Build rapport • Build trust • Build relationships • Build influence • Build confidence •

What is entropy? Entropy is a measure of the disorder in a system. For example, in a box full of gas, the molecules are moving around at random. The disorder is high. As the gas is heated, the molecules move faster and faster until they are all moving at the same speed. The disorder is lower.
